<section>
	<h2>What Is It?</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>
			<a href="https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/microdata.html">Microdata</a>
			applies semantic meaning to your existing HTML
		</li>
		<li>
			This makes it easier for web crawlers to understand the data in the HTML
		</li>
	</ul>
</section>

<section>
	<h2>What Does It Look Like?</h2>

  <img src="/assets/images/mr_robot_imdb_episode_list.png">

	<aside class="notes">
		<p>The following code is an adapted/improved example from IMDB from every hackers favorite show, Mr. Robot</p>
	</aside>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>Without Microdata</h2>

  <pre>
    <code class="lang-html">
&lt;div id="episodes_content"&gt;
  &lt;h3 id="episode_top"&gt;Season 1&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;div class="list detail eplist"&gt;
    &lt;div class="list_item odd"&gt;
      &lt;div class="image"&gt;
        &lt;img alt="eps1.0_hellofriend.mov" src="http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/eps1.0_hellofriend.mov.jpg"&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;S1, Ep1&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;

      &lt;div&gt;
        &lt;div class="airdate"&gt;24 Jun. 2015&lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;a href="/title/tt4652838/?ref_=ttep_ep1"&gt;eps1.0_hellofriend.mov&lt;/&gt;
        &lt;div class="item_description"&gt;
            A notorious hacker takes an interest in cyber-security engineer and vigilante-styled computer hacker Elliot; and an evil corporation is hacked.
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
    </code>
  </pre>
</section>

<section>
  <h2>With Microdata</h2>
  <pre>
    <code class="lang-html">
&lt;div id="episodes_content" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/TVSeries"&gt;
  &lt;meta itemprop="name" content="Mr. Robot (TV Series 2015â€“ )"&gt;
  &lt;h3 id="episode_top" itemprop="name"&gt;Season 1&lt;/h3&gt;
  &lt;div class="list detail eplist"&gt;
    &lt;div class="list_item odd"&gt;
      &lt;div class="image"&gt;
        &lt;img alt="eps1.0_hellofriend.mov" src="http://ia.media-imdb.com/images/eps1.0_hellofriend.mov.jpg"&gt;
        &lt;div&gt;S1, Ep1&lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;

      &lt;div itemprop="episodes" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/TVEpisode"&gt;
        &lt;meta itemprop="episodeNumber" content="1"&gt;
        &lt;time class="airdate" itemprop="datePublished" content="2015-06-24"&gt;24 Jun. 2015&lt;/time&gt;
        &lt;a href="/title/tt4652838/?ref_=ttep_ep1" title="eps1.0_hellofriend.mov" itemprop="name"&gt;eps1.0_hellofriend.mov&lt;/&gt;
        &lt;div class="item_description" itemprop="description"&gt;
            A notorious hacker takes an interest in cyber-security engineer and vigilante-styled computer hacker Elliot; and an evil corporation is hacked.
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
    </code>
  </pre>

  <aside class="notes">
    * Note the use of the meta tag for information you don't want to display
    * You can stack attributes to make it more descriptive (i.e. `name`)
  </aside>
</section>
